The paper deals with graph decompositions and multicuts, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the convex hull of characteristic functions, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and optimization (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses lifting of multicuts, which is a topic in signal processing and image analysis (cs.SI).
